Cell.Data: Customer Sample Standards Model Compliance for C / C++
Procedure is not reducible in terms of intervals.
Procedure has more than one entry point.
Procedure has more than one exit point.
Function does not return a value on all paths.
Actual parameter is also global to procedure.
Defined parameter has possible clear path.
Parameters do not match expected actions.
Referenced parameter has possible clear path.
Global used in procedure matches local parameter.
Procedure definition has no associated prototype.
Variable should be defined once in only one file.
Procedure name re-used in different files.
Modification of loop counter in loop body.
UR anomaly, variable used before assignment.
Named variable declared but not used in code.
More than *** executable reformatted lines in file.
No brackets to loop body (added by Testbed).
No brackets to then/else (added by Testbed).
Procedural para used in an uncalled procedure.
Use of obsolete language feature ( use = - ).
Loop control expression may not terminate loop.
Use of break statement in loop.
No parameters declared in proc specification.
Static procedure is not explicitly called in code analysed.
Loop index is not declared locally.
No default case in switch statement.
Use of shift operator on signed type.
Switch case not terminated with break.
Duplicate use of a name in an enumeration.
Function use is not a call.
A #if has no #endif in the same file.
Reference parameter to procedure is reassigned.
Use of ++ or -- on RHS of && or || operator.
Volatile variable accessed on RHS of && or ||.
Declaration types do not match across a system.
